Feature: the assign_scenarios to work_done loop runs under fabro orchestration with emit_r as the sole in-graph work_done emitter

  Fabro DOT loop-graph contract — ADR-051 (Implementer-to-Reviewer graph with emit_r as the
  SOLE gated work_done emitter, ENFORCED by native script= scoping), Anchored on ADR-048
  (invariant #4: the shop-msg protocol is preserved). Evidence: findings/fabro-spike/
  05-structural-loop.md section 1(b)/(c) (loop fidelity GREEN on live non-dry-run) and
  04-goal-demo.md. Non-judgment nodes are native script= steps with no LLM agency; work_done
  round-trips over shop-msg (ADR-018), not over fabro structured outputs, and the lead harvests
  it via shop-msg read outbox — never by reading fabro child outputs. This is a LEAD-PROCESS
  contract pin with no current BC addressee; NOT dispatchable via assign_scenarios, flagged for
